{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 15:20:30.946019", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission successful.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1]\n- root_cause_name: [link_down]\n\nRecommended immediate remediation steps you can run (optional, not applied):\n1. On each switch (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1):\n   - ip link set ovs-system up\n   - ip link set <bridge_name> up   (e.g., ip link set leaf_1 up)\n   - Verify LOCAL port state: ovs-ofctl show <bridge_name>\n2. Check kernel OVS datapath and logs:\n   - ovs-dpctl show\n   - journalctl -u openvswitch-switch --no-pager\n   - lsmod | grep openvswitch\n3. If systemctl reports inactive while daemons run, consider restarting the service cleanly:\n   - systemctl restart openvswitch-switch\n   - Verify processes and service state: systemctl status openvswitch-switch; ps aux | egrep 'ovsdb|ovs-vswitchd'\n4. If restarting causes processes to exit or LOCAL ports remain down, inspect /var/log/openvswitch/*.log for errors and consider reloading kernel modules or rebooting the device after gathering logs.\n\nIf you want, I can run the follow-up diagnostics (ovs-dpctl, logs, ip link manipulations) and provide exact commands and expected outputs before you apply changes.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2433, "output_tokens": 301, "total_tokens": 2734, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
